{"word":"δονέω","slug":"δονέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δονέω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to shake</i>, of wind, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>δ. γάλα</el> <i>to shake</i> it, as to make butter, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to drive about</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>agitare</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἡ Ἀσίη ἐδονέετο</el> Asia <i>was in commotion</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>αἰθὴρ δονεῖται</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}